# Core Product Consistency

- Consistency with existing product patterns is more important than novelty.
- Reuse existing files and components before introducing a new pattern.
- If nearby examples conflict, prefer the documented canon in `docs/ux-constitution.md`, `docs/api-conventions.md`, and `docs/golden-examples.md`.
- Call out any intentional deviation from existing UX, API, terminology, or accessibility patterns before implementing it.
- Prefer stable curling-domain terminology. Do not casually rename concepts like member, spare request, league, sheet, draw, bonspiel, or event.
- For reviews, check work against `docs/consistency-review-checklist.md`. For forms, also verify `docs/accessibility-checklist.md` (label association and visible focus).
